      "href": "/dozzyrok/list/maximalist-cinema/",
      "user": "dozzyrok",
      "slug": "maximalist-cinema",
      "title": "Maximalist Cinema",
      "desc": "Maximalism is the abundance of ideas, concepts, styles, feelings. All ingredients thrown into the mix, and assorted to all be in view. Narratively or Visually, it is an overload of the senses, it is the essence of ADHD. Taking the clutter, and making it beautiful (Not all of these are movies I enjoy but most of them are)\nNOT ON LETTERBOXD:\n*Adventures of Peppré Ann & Froends\n*RANG ZULU",
      "owner": "List by Dozzyrok PATRON",
      "tags": []
    },
    {
      "href": "/prime4illusion/list/maximalist-cinema/",
      "user": "prime4illusion",
      "slug": "maximalist-cinema",
      "title": "Maximalist Cinema",
      "desc": "Maximalist cinema doesn't just refer to the scale of the filmmaking (though that's often a factor), it also refers to the scale of emotional impact which is why films like Texas Chainsaw Massacre are here.",
      "owner": "List by maddy",
      "tags": []
    },
    {
      "href": "/mprs/list/maximalist-cinema/",
      "user": "mprs",
      "slug": "maximalist-cinema",
      "title": "Maximalist Cinema",
      "desc": "I've been thinking a lot about maximalism in the last few days, the way filmmaking highlights it - making sure you feel just how fucking gigantic the film is - and how it impacts both the film's narrative and future films like it. I might do a little writing about it soon, so I've decided to make this list as a point of reference; suggestions are encouraged, especially when you consider that a lot of these movies aren't even good in the first place",
      "owner": "List by Lydie 💜 PATRON",
      "tags": []
    },
    {
      "href": "/miche341/list/maximalist-cinema/",
      "user": "miche341",
      "slug": "maximalist-cinema",
      "title": "Maximalist Cinema",
      "desc": "These are movies that employ my favorite design concept: Maximalism. I absolutely adore sensory overload and complexity, have it be in the narrative or the style. These movies try their hardest to assault all of your senses and never let you take a breath. Get ready. (Not all of these are movies I enjoy but most of them are)\nNOT ON LETTERBOXD:\n*Adventures of Peppré Ann & Froends\n*RANG ZULU",
      "owner": "List by miche341",
      "tags": []
